The Africa Centres for Disease Control and Prevention (Africa CDC) has said that there are now 7,123 confirmed cases of Coronavirus (COVID-19) in 50 countries across Africa. The health agency stated this in a tweet on its official Twitter account on Friday evening. According to the tweet, COVID-19 had killed 289 people in Africa, while a total of 592 patients have recovered from the deadly disease across the continent. “#COVID19 – SURVEILLANCE UPDATE “50@_AfricanUnion Member States reporting 7,123 COVID-19 cases, 289 deaths, and 592 recoveries by region.” DAILY POST recalls that Africa CDC had also provided an update on Coronavirus on Friday morning.